76561197970599675,Not Recommended,307960,13733598,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,kazale1,"I had high hopes for this sim, as I loved the original IL2 Forgotten Battles, and have high regard for Studio 777's Rise of Flight, on whose engine (and business model), this is based. Without a demo, the only guidance I had on how this would play was something along the lines of, take Rise of Flight as a benchmark. Rise of Flight, though not maxed out, is smooth and fast on my machine, and looks excellent, so with not much hesitation, I took the plunge.I didn't mind so much reports of few aircraft and skill points to gain unlocks, nor that there was only one map with one season.  When I ran the sim, though, my greatest disappointment was its performance. On my quad 2 q6600 2.40gh, GTX 750, 6 gig DDR2 ram system I can still get pretty much anything to play well with a bit of tweaking, ROF especially (and even IL2 Cliffs of Dover, which everyone considers somewhat of a dog), but IL2 BOS stands out in that it is the worst of the bunch. I can't get framer rates over 30, and am plagued with micro pauses and stutters.Normally, I would just tinker with the graphics options and find some option causing the problem, but here, I don't have that option. The developers have taken the stunning decision to lock the public out of the advanced settings and give you low, balanced, high and ultra. There are a couple of other options - screen resolution, shader amount (4,2,0), muliple grachics cards checkbox, and a cinematics checkbox hidden in the camera menu, but that's it. And, as far as I can tell from the official forum, there are no plans to open up the toolbox. It seems we gamers can't be trusted to mess with things.So, this means I have a sim which runs poorly and looks bland. Not ideal.What else?The vulnerability of the aircraft is somewhat absurd. I tend to fly the 109 mostly, and fly straight and and level and away from the enemy, and you might just stay in the air. Other than that, it's a case of a couple of passes and usually a wrecked engine from either the enemy or one of many mechanical. I've yet to actually shoot anything down so ludicrous is the damage modelling. If this is accurate, then it flies in the face of every single other sim I've flown (and that's about all of them).I have to admit to haveing just bought the FW190. It was on sale and I see it as a hedge hedge against the future where the developers might just open the graphics options and address the fragility issues (these things can happen).You probably know all the other stuff - no evidence of any real battle in the city of Stalingrad, no Bf 110, no Ju 52 (though both seem possibilities - for purchase, of course).Oh, and my last gripe - the IL2 itself is the single seat without the rear gunner. Damnation. I used to love playing as the rear gunner."
