76561198356927762,Recommended,307960,28997803,Posted: 3 January,all,RufusPompeii,"~HOW TO GET THE MOST FROM BATTLE OF STALINGRAD~-You need a JOYSTICK. Assign ELEVATOR and STABILIZER trims to the vertical axis of the hat switch. Assign ROLL trim to the horizontal axis of the hat switch. Use the hat switch with your thumb to stabilize your airplane in flight.-Adjust the response curve of your joystick in the KEY MAPPING options. There will be an option for all 3 axis of your joystick, ROLL, PITCH, and YAW.  Move the SENSITIVITY slider to between 75% - 90%. If your control response is still too sensitive increase the slider. Decrease the slider if the control response is sluggish.-Developers did not include anything like what most gamers would call a 'Campaign' or 'Story Mode'. BOS has a template for the community to create new scripted campaigns. The game is basically unplayable as a single player without installing some additional campaigns. These are available for free to download at the official forums:https://forum.il2sturmovik.com/"
