76561198054540582,Recommended,307960,18041490,"Posted: 15 September, 2015",all,Jon Snow,"If you are an offline player like myself, you will be left wanting more from the campaign.The game incorporates some very familiar elements from 777 and 1C.However it is a shame that the cockpit is not clickable, which is fine for ROF but in more complex aircraft, I was hoping for a IL2 ClOD situation.The campaign is not your classic campaign, I would say that it is almost the bare minimum. You are not part of a squadron, you do not fly consecutive missions which have a feeling of progression like in IL2 1946. basically you click an airfield like in ROF and choose a mission. Every time.....no airfield transfers, no front movements in the chapter, you can even switch sides every mission, there is also no time progression.For each mission you get XP. Expert mode gets you more XP, as well as safely landing your aircraft. With morexp come more unlocks, which don't actually hinder the game, and don't really keep you from enjoying the game if you don't have them.When you get enough XP, the next chapter simply becomes available. There is is still a lot of work to be done here because honestly in reference to ROF, this campaign is not even beta, it is sub par.That being said the game is IN development. The campaign system IS being addressed and I am very excited for the announced upcoming updates. Maybe when the game has a more stable and finished overall environment developed Desastersoft could pick it up, who knows. The thing is the Devs are really working hard on making this game up to their own personal standards (despite various financing problems and the fact that this isn't a very sim firendly market)The game is a good successor to IL2 1946. It just needs polishing, but IL2 1946 WAS a much simpler game, where you could add new planes in a months time. This is not possible with the level of detail in BOS.The map is huge and wonderful. Cockpits and planes look fantastic. The gun effects, explosions, lighting it is all very next gen. It is a huuuuge improvement and a great leap forward.Even though I am honestly not entirely satisfied, I would 10/10 recommend this game. It's going places, and if you want to fly the IL2 or other iconic Soviet aircraft, then this is the way to go, for me not even IL2 1946 is a worthy substitute."
