76561197966626112,Not Recommended,307960,33310124,Posted: 6 July,all,Pablo,"I bought this game for VR functionality, and I have quite enjoyed flying around in the HTC Vive. Performance is a bit of an issue, as I cannot get 90 frames per second even on low detail. The cockpits look very good, though there are often issues with camera placement and drifting, which I haven't really had with other games.The main positives for this game are sound design, graphics and realism. I'm not a big fan of arcade flight sims and I really enjoy the difficulty and satisfaction of scoring even one kill in this game.However, the amount of content on offer for £40 is frankly a joke. You only have access to eight planes, though a couple of additional ones are available for ludicrous prices. The campaign mode and mission builder feel severely stunted compared to previous il-2 games. I miss the variety of 1946, Pacfic Fighters and the original. If you don't have a VR headset, the only reason to buy this is the graphical upgrade.The DRM is also a total pain in the neck. You need an internet connection to play the campaign (thanks for that, guys) and I frequently have to alt+F4 to restart the sign-in process which occurs at the start of every session.I will probably get my money's worth out of it as I bought it on sale and have a VR headset. However I feel very let down by the developers whom I previously admired and seem to have just gotten greedy. It's a no from me."
