cal air-warfare of gameplay... (but impossible actually about pc ressources and fps rate, of course)...but yeah, i'll try to not be too rude anymore, lolall these bad xps waste a good part of personnal entertainment, or patience, or immersion to play with BoS but these bad points must not be the only thing to remember, i think...so, globaly, i'am very mixed between positive and negative opinion for BoS. :)i enjoyed 1946 during years, but when u have started IL2 BoS, difficult to enjoy 1946 as u did before, 3D level and realism (particulary concerning straffing, ground details, or bombing events) are trully better here/now in BoS and its hard to get back in 1946 for a part just because of that... its simply no more the same now, and 1946 looks basic in comparison !but in the same time, all these issues broken a significant part of my xp/fun to play with BoS since i bought BoM (without take count of huge patience needed to set everything, that i was ready to do it... but many players wouldnt or couldnt have patience for, i am definatly sure of that !).soooo... :/ (let stay on ""mixed advice"" globaly, its more simple to say)of course, beside that (lets be more positive for last chapter), it must not be forgotten:it stay one of 2or3major refs if u like true flight sims (for realism and challenging gameplay), no doubt about it !and its for sure the best graphical xp u could have in all existing flight sims concerning ""prop fighters and WW2""...(again, if you enjoy realism, mostly... arcade its different, there are many more games there, but its such more basic and few realist compared with BoS or DCS then it cant be compared together...but Il2 BoS can provide both styles, depending of options chosen by each players, wich is also a good point for this game, more different types of players can find what they want in BoS, wich is cool too)...but imo, compared with all other games dispo, and strictly in a realistic perspective, and also strictly about graphism environment (opposed to tactical realism as i said above): BoS is the best of all for prop fighters warfare on pc games already existing.CONCLUSION:if u are a fanatic of flight sims, u need BoS !definatly, its sure u'll enjoy it. (y) :)but in the same time, after some months of play, there are real frustrations and real dissapointments too.... :'((well, let's be honest here too: its the case for 99% of all games and all styles of games ! so, that can not be a argument vs BoS)globaly, i still recommend this game, of course...(even if mixed advice seems me much more closer of what i feel on the long term, but that doesnt change the fact then BoS worth positive recommendation without any doubt)BUT there still things to fix ! (that must not be minimized in judgment)..for that, like often as gamer, lets be patient and see with time... ^^"
