76561198059743496,Recommended,307960,13012249,"Posted: 19 November, 2014",all,ToeTag,"Casual simmer’s view:Updated review.A lot has changed since the initial review. The developers deserve a lot of credit for the game’s continuous improvements and excellent communication with the community.The game looks fantastic and now offers three regions, Stalingrad, Moscow, and the soon-to-be released Kuban area, which takes players from the mostly flat, relatively featureless plains and forests of the Russian interior to and brings the fight to an area with oceans and large hills. The new theater also presents elements of air-to-surface combat with the introduction of medium size surface combatants, submarines, and transports. The Moscow and Stalingrad areas are no longer restricted to snowy landscapes with other seasonal maps available for each.The game’s plane set continues to expand with a wide selection of aircraft ranging from fighters to medium bombers to transports. Most importantly the developers make frequent flight, weapons, and damage modeling adjustments based on newly discovered or reanalyzed data and flight testing. As with every flight simulation, armchair BOx pilots will continue to debate flight modeling until the sun blows up, but the developers’ willingness to tweak things is very encouraging as the game expands.The silly unlocks are thankfully long gone, but the base singleplayer campaign is still horrible. The missions remain incredibly formulaic and repetitive, and friendly AI is so bad that I don’t even bother to acknowledge my wingman or flight’s presence. The game will receive a new career mode that should improve the singleplayer experience to hopefully bring it up to par with the rest of the game’s improvements. As the simulation currently stands I’d give it an 8/10 with potential to go higher with AI and campaign improvements."
