76561198173170335,Recommended,307960,35508494,Posted: 5 October,all,Spitfire976,"This is the best WW2 fighter simulator in the market, though it's way too expensive. This is not a game of every one, but there's a fine game to see if this game is for you, War Thunder. If you like it, and wish to take the experience to the next level, this is the game for doing it.The value is questionable in the content departament, eight planes for 60 dollars or 19,99 dollars for a collector plane is hardly a good selling point, and the single player content is decent but not worth the full price. This game true selling point is the online content, despite having only a coupple of full servers, it's the most imersive fighter pilot experience you'll find. Like DCS, though at a much better value, you'll be paying a premium for the experience, so this should not be your first fighter simulator. But if you like the genre and ww2 combat this is a must buy.A word of warning if you buy outside steam, I'd recomend buying Battle of Stalingrad first, as it's planes are used on both Battle of Kuban and Battle of Moscow."
